text: NSYNC is the first studio album by American boy band NSYNC. It was released on May 26, 1997 in Germany and on March 24, 1998 in the United States. It reached number 2 on the Billboard 200. ==Track listing== All lead vocals provided by JC Chasez and Justin Timberlake. ;Notes * signifies an additional producer * "I Just Wanna Be with You" contains portions of "Family Affair" by Sly Stone. ==References== Category:1997 albums Category:Debut albums Category:NSYNC albums Category:Pop albums
title: 'N Sync (album)
